parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become stuck or difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels sticky or notchy
making it difficult to maintain a straight line or control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to fires, and potentially result in accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger occupancy mat can prevent the airbag from deploying in the event of an accident, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on the dashboard
passenger airbag deactivation light always on

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Battery and Charging System Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause unexpected stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Wheel and Airbag System Failure (Spring Failure)

console controls for air conditioner and heater replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical components can cause fires, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Seat Occupancy Mat (OC3) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat occupancy mat can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating that the passenger airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: the airbag system malfunction warning lamp on the dashboard comes on and remains on
the passenger seat airbag sensor mat fails without stress on the seat
the passenger airbag defaults to off condition.
